  "prompt": "How do I tell Google to deindex my all pages site?",
  "response": "To request Google to deindex your entire website, you have several options:\n\n1. Use robots.txt\n- Add this to your robots.txt file:\n```\nUser-agent: *\nDisallow: /\n```\n\n2. Add noindex meta tag\n- Place this in the <head> section of every page:\n```html\n<meta name=\"robots\" content=\"noindex\">\n```\n\n3. Google Search Console\n- Log in to Search Console\n- Select your property\n- Go to \"Removals\" \n- Click \"New Request\"\n- Choose \"Temporary removal\" or \"Remove entire site\"\n\n4. Remove site from Search Console\n- Remove your site property entirely from Search Console\n\n5. Submit removal request\n- Use Google Search Console's URL removal tool\n- Request removal of your entire domain\n\nPro tips:\n- Combination of methods is most effective\n- Wait 24-48 hours for full deindexing\n- Verify removal by searching site:yourdomain.com\n\nChoose the method that best fits your specific situation.",
